fy, rent, lease, loan, sell, assign, distribute, perform, display, license, reverse engineer, or create derivative works based on the Site or any Content (including without limitation, any software). Copyright notice Unless otherwise noted, the graphic images, buttons, text and other Content contained in this Site are the exclusive property of Jones Lang LaSalle and its licensors. Except for personal use, these items may not be copied, distributed, displayed, reproduced, or transmitted, in any form or by any means, electronic, mechanical, photocopying, recording, or otherwise without prior written permission of Jones Lang LaSalle, or where applicable the third-party licensor and/or owner of the Content. Trademarks This Site features logos, brand identities and other trademarks and service marks (collectively, the \" Marks \") that are the property of, or are licensed to Jones Lang LaSalle and its subsidiaries. Nothing contained on this Site should be construed as granting, by implication, estoppel, or otherwise, any license or right to use any Mark displayed on this Site without written permission of Jones Lang LaSalle or any such third party that may own a Mark displayed on the Site. Owner Content Jones Lang LaSalle may, in its sole discretion, permit Owners to post, upload, publish, submit and transmit Content and information (collectively, “ Owner Content ”) to the Site. If you are an Owner, by providing Owner Content to any portion of the Site, you grant to Jones Lang LaSalle a perpetual, royalty-free, revocable, worldwide, non-exclusive license (with the right to sublicense to users) to reproduce, adapt, translate, publish, publicly perform and display, distribute, create derivative works from, store and otherwise use your Owner Content for any purpose (whether promotion, marketing, commercial or otherwise), on or in connection with the Site (including the Services). You are solely responsible for the Owner Content you provide. Jones Lang LaSalle will not be li